# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Self-adoption Runbook

This runbook covers how Sula manages itself as a first-class consumer.

## Required Files

- `.sula/project.toml`
- `.sula/version.lock`
- `STATUS.md`
- `CHANGE-RECORDS.md`
- `docs/change-records/`
- `docs/releases/`
- `docs/incidents/`

## Workflow

1. treat Sula root as a project with durable memory
2. keep the root manifest aligned with the `sula-core` profile
3. regenerate the root memory digest after non-trivial work
4. keep the canary and root self-adoption both passing `doctor --strict`

## Guardrail

Do not twist Sula Core into a one-project template just to satisfy self-adoption. The profile must still remain reusable for similar operating-system repositories.
